    "### Satistical Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "787d0396",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Key Inferences\n",
    "* YearBuilt, GrLivArea, TotalBsmtSF and GarageArea are related to the slae price\n",
    "* BuiltQual, Electrical, FullBath, GarageType and GarageCars are affecting the SalePrice "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 121,
   "id": "b0178950",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Lets explore yearbuilt and Saleprice statistically"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 122,
   "id": "c435b617",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "ShapiroResult(statistic=0.8717886209487915, pvalue=1.371634693338205e-32)\n",
      "ShapiroResult(statistic=0.9247534275054932, pvalue=4.7268936789807727e-26)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Assumptions : Data must be normal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ho: The data is normal\n",
    "# Ha: The data is not normal\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(stats.shapiro(data['SalePrice']))\n",
    "print(stats.shapiro(data['YearBuilt']))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Since both pvalues are less than 0.05 we have to reject Ho. SO we can go with spearman's correlation\n",
    "# test (non parametric)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 123,
   "id": "d852ed28",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "SignificanceResult(statistic=0.6554334366989801, pvalue=7.731685842769625e-175)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Spearman's correlation test\n",
    "# Ho: Samples are independent\n",
    "# Ha: Samples are dependent\n",
    "\n",
    "print(stats.spearmanr(data['SalePrice'],data['YearBuilt']))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 124,
   "id": "52183e87",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "SignificanceResult(statistic=0.6554334366989801, pvalue=7.731685842769625e-175)\n",
      "SignificanceResult(statistic=0.610789140940605, pvalue=9.424659979319682e-146)\n",
      "SignificanceResult(statistic=0.7352976571006725, pvalue=1.7737764527778764e-241)\n",
      "SignificanceResult(statistic=0.6598555665561451, pvalue=5.419048779956526e-178)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for i in num_cols:\n",
    "    if i != 'SalePrice':\n",
    "        print(stats.spearmanr(data['SalePrice'],data[i]))"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 127,
   "id": "de2494b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "KruskalResult(statistic=440.6623751087267, pvalue=5.0735517569761e-93)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Kruskal Walli's Test\n",
    "# Ho: mu1=mu2=...mu6\n",
    "# Ha: atleast one mean is different\n",
    "\n",
    "s1 = data[data['GarageType']=='Attchd']['SalePrice']\n",
    "s2 = data[data['GarageType']=='Detchd']['SalePrice']\n",
    "s3 = data[data['GarageType']=='BuiltIn']['SalePrice']\n",
    "s4 = data[data['GarageType']=='CarPort']['SalePrice']\n",
    "s5 = data[data['GarageType']=='Basment']['SalePrice']\n",
    "s6 = data[data['GarageType']=='2Types']['SalePrice']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(stats.kruskal(s1,s2,s3,s4,s5,s6))"
   ]
  },

    "# Missing value Value\n",
    "\n",
    "# Closest fit\n",
    "# Central Value imputation\n",
    "# Deletion (Lot of data is missing in a column or very few rows in the data\n",
    "# has missing columns)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 134,
   "id": "afa52dc8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div>\n",

       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "MannwhitneyuResult(statistic=201362.0, pvalue=1.842459050609252e-14)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 147,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Lets validate this statically\n",
    "# Ho: The samples are independent\n",
    "# Ha: The samples are dependent\n",
    "\n",
    "stats.mannwhitneyu(data[data['Fence']==0]['SalePrice'],\n",
    "                  data[data['Fence']==1]['SalePrice'])"

    "# Lets cap the outliers to 99th percentile in GarageArea,\n",

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 183,
   "id": "5f17bd05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def model_scores(trainx,trainy,testx,testy,model):\n",
    "    m = model\n",
    "    m.fit(trainx,trainy)\n",
    "    pred = m.predict(testx)\n",
    "    print('R_Square:',r2_score(testy,pred))\n",
    "    print('MSE:',mean_squared_error(testy,pred))\n",
    "    print('RMSE:',np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(testy,pred)))\n",
    "    print('MAPE:',mean_absolute_percentage_error(testy,pred))\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 184,
   "id": "48c0cce9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "R_Square: 0.7953925371660249\n",
      "MSE: 1271149362.7174106\n",
      "RMSE: 35653.181663315976\n",
      "MAPE: 0.1527954715571055\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Test Data\n",
    "\n",
    "model_scores(x_train,y_train,x_test,y_test,LinearRegression())"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "46953e0f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Forward Selection Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "36e8981a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Algorith:(remove)\n",
    "1. It starts from the null model.\n",
    "2. It adds the feature with the highest correlation with target in the model.\n",
    "3. Its picks the second column from the remaining dataset with the highest correlation.\n",
    "4. It build the model adding the new feature to it.\n",
    "5. This repeats until it has included all the columns.\n",
    "\n",
    "Use can pass number of columns he want to select or he can find the number of columns with best score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bc8466a7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Backward Selection Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7d08e5af",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Algorithm:(add)\n",
    "1. Its starts with full model.\n",
    "2. It removes the columns which is least significant(highest p_value)\n",
    "3. It again fits a model with k-1 features.\n",
    "4. Again it will remove the columns which is least significant\n",
    "5. It will repeat until all the columns are exahusted.\n",
    "\n",
    "Use can pass number of columns he want to select or he can find the number of columns with best score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 286,
   "id": "c02d8c8c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "                                 k_features='best',\n",
    "                                 scoring='r2',\n",
    "                                 cv=3,\n",
    "                                 verbose=0,forward=False)"
   ]
  },

    "### RFE(Recursive Feature Elimination)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c5cd3600",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": []
  },
  {
